globalblocking-block-reason-dropdown:
Options that appear in the dropdown list of pre-defined reasons on the GlobalBlocking block special page.

In the format of a wikitext list. Line with one "*" are categories and lines with two "*" characters are items which can be selected by the user.

Similar to {{msg-mw|ipbreason-dropdown}}

globalblocking-block-edit-dropdown:
Shown beneath the global block form on the right side. It is a link to {{msg-mw|globalblocking-block-reason-dropdown|notext=1}} message allowing administrators to customise it on their wiki.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|ipb-edit-dropdown}}

globalblocking-block-expiry:
After the colon, the user can enter a timestamp on which the block automatically ends or a time period like "1 hour", "2 days", "1 year" etc. But in English only because the time period is parsed by the underlying OS, not by MediaWiki.

{{Identical|Expiry}}

Identical to the message {{msg-mw|block-expiry}} and used in the same context.

